observations.recommendation:
For the Local Chief Executive to:
1) require and provide the necessary support for the identification of PDAF balances that have remained outstanding in the books for several years. If properly identified, ensure immediate settlement of such total balance by remitting it to the national treasury so that funds can be utilized by the national government;
2) require the implementing offices or departments to draw up the appropriate project proposals to utilize fully idle or dormant trust funds pursuant to the law governing said grant and/or Memorandum of Agreement/contract with the respective source agencies;
3) direct the Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Heads of implementing departments, to implement proper liquidation of the amount granted as well as the refund of excess project funds to the source agency or request for transfer to its General Fund, if so provided in the terms of the grant;
4) require the implementing offices or departments to execute without delay the intended PPAs of the fund transfers so that the benefits derived therefrom may already be enjoyed by the intended beneficiaries;
5) direct the Municipal Accountant to properly classify and record the transactions in its various appropriate account titles (under corresponding subsidiary ledgers) to have a more reliable balance of accounts to be presented in the financial statements;
6) henceforth, every implementing department should ensure the existence of necessary documents such as agreements, other related guidelines or approved work and financial plan of every fund received for proper recording, timely implementation and effective monitoring;
7) direct the Municipal Treasurer, in coordination with the accounting department, to observe timely and full remittance of all collections accruing to the national government in accordance with the existing laws, rules and regulations; and
8) the Accounting Department, in coordination with the implementing departments to perform reconciliation and record the necessary adjusting entries of those dormant/non-moving fund transfers. Once reconciled but there are still remaining unadjusted balances, gather the required documents necessary to file the request for authority to write-off dormant fund transfers such as certification by the chief accountants and approved by the heads of the source and implementing agencies that the fund was utilized for the purpose, and certification from the recipient that the project was partially or fully implemented, supported by pictures of the implemented projects.

For management to direct the MDRRM Council and implementing departments/offices to:
15) the MDRRM Council, headed by the Municipal Mayor, prepare the STF balance for the DRRM Fund as a result of fully completed PPAs and considers its re-appropriation to other DRRM PPAs that remained unfunded. Also, evaluate the status of unimplemented PPAs for realignment or reversion;
16) the implementing departments headed by the Municipal Mayor through the DRRM Officer, follow the schedule of implementation of pre-disaster PPAs as embodied in the approved DRRM Investment Plans. In coordination with the Engineering Department, fully evaluate causes of delays to provide immediate resolution;
17) the MDRRM Council, through the DRRM Officer, prepare the Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF and ensure reconciliation with other reports and submit to COA within prescribed period;
18) the Municipal Accountant, in coordination with MEO and MDRRMO, re-evaluate documents and reports related to pending projects under the Special Trust Fund to properly report implementation status and revert unutilized balances of STF from CY 2017 and prior to the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund;
19) the Municipal Accountant prepare the Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF, ensure details reconcile with other financial reports and disclose in the notes to financial statements any other information necessary to substantiate variances between books of account and other financial records; and
20) the Municipal Accountant to submit the Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF to the audit team within the prescribed period.

observations.reason:
Reconciliation of a portion of the STF balance is on-going;
Implementation of DRRM PPAs are still on-going due to various constraints;
Submitted Reports are not within prescribed period or incomplete;
Re-evaluation of documents charged against STF is on-going;
Monthly Reports prepared quarterly rather than monthly;
Submission to COA not always within prescribed period.

